cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL 

The paper discusses deep neural networks (DNNs) and their known problems, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper's focus on robustness to adversarial inputs suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of security and privacy (cs.CR) and systems and control (cs.SY), but these are less likely given the emphasis on DNNs.
